1112
00:59:38,221 --> 00:59:42,517
Your Honor, may I ask our team's Ms. Yoo
to make arguments from now on?

1113
00:59:42,600 --> 00:59:44,102
Yes, you may proceed.

1114
00:59:46,187 --> 00:59:47,355
Ms. Yoo.

1115
00:59:48,690 --> 00:59:49,524
Yes, sir.

1116
00:59:57,573 --> 00:59:59,659
I've always been curious.

1117
01:00:00,326 --> 01:00:02,495
Those persistent comments online.

1118
01:00:02,578 --> 01:00:05,540
How many people are actually behind them?

1119
01:00:05,623 --> 01:00:10,128
Are we mistaking an anonymous minority
for the unspecified majority?

1120
01:00:10,211 --> 01:00:12,046
So, we've verified it

1121
01:00:13,131 --> 01:00:15,550
with the help of our colleague
with exceptional IT skills.

1122
01:00:18,803 --> 01:00:21,097
We've marked the IP addresses

1123
01:00:21,180 --> 01:00:24,308
of those who wrote
these anonymous posts and comments

1124
01:00:24,392 --> 01:00:26,769
with cute animal icons.

1125
01:00:27,437 --> 01:00:28,479
Like this.

1126
01:00:34,736 --> 01:00:35,737
Why are they the same?

1127
01:00:36,362 --> 01:00:38,573
-It's a rat.
-Did one person write them all?

1128
01:00:38,656 --> 01:00:40,992
Do you see these mice icons?

1129
01:00:41,743 --> 01:00:42,910
Isn't it shocking?

1130
01:00:42,994 --> 01:00:45,329
Out of 250 comments,

1131
01:00:45,413 --> 01:00:47,957
